Nigerian singer, Oladapo Daniel Oyebanjo, aka D’Banj marked his 42ndbirthday in grand style at the Ebony Place in Victoria Island, Lagos. The event which kicked-off with an opening prayer by actress Beverly Osu, had Deejay Obi on the wheels creating the celebrative mood, and saw performances from a few of the last season’s The Nigerian Idol, of which D’banj was a music coach. Celebrities present at the event to celebrate with the ‘You Don Make Me Fall In Love’ singer include singer and rapper, Ice Prince; singer, Skiibii; TV host, IK Osagioduwa, Frank Edoho (You Want To Be A Millionaire host); Wande Coal, actor, Ikechukwu; YCee; D’banj’s wife, Lineo among others.  